result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jonathon Martin Ciboski in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 16CM6 and 15CT70 @ 3:06 p.m. Agreement - Def will plead to 15CT70 ct 1, dismiss and consolidate ct 2, dismiss and read in 16CM6. $2655.00 fine and costs, 170 days jail w/credit for 4 days served, good time, huber, 30 months revocation, 1 yr IID, AODA and driver safety plan. Atty Schuster agrees. Court questions length of IID. Statement by Atty Schuster. Def understands and agrees with stated agreement. Plea quest. reviewed. Plea to ct 1 guilty. BAC .23. Court consolidates and dismisses ct 2. 16CM6 dismissed and read in. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Schuster satisfied. Court finds Def understands and plea freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts plea and finds guilty of ct 1 OWI 4th. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Statement by Defendant. Remarks by the Court. Court approves agreement. $2,655.00 fine and costs, 170 days jail, credit for 4 days served, 30 months revocation, 1 yr IID, AODA and follow through. Huber. Sentence commence immediately. Apply bonds from both cases. DNA sample. Pmt for balance. Postconviction rights.
Plea/sentencing hearing on June 22, 2016 at 09:00 am.

Attorney Jessica L Schuster in court.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Written authorization filed.  Statement by Atty Schuster.  Def has posted $1000.00 cash bond.  Complaint received, reviewed.  Not guitly plea entered.  Atty Schuster will obtain def's signature for bond  Status conference scheduled for February 1, 2016 at 03:30 pm.
